fields.content:
1. All residents can drop-off their trees to be recycled into mulch. To drop your tree off at Zilker Park, remove any ornaments, lighting, decorations, and stands from your tree. Trees with flocking, or fake-snow, will not be accepted.

  2. Do not place in a plastic bag.

  3. Drop your tree off between 10am and 2pm on one of the following days:

    1. Saturday, December 30, 2017

    2. Sunday, December 31, 2017

    3. Saturday, January 6, 2018

    4. Sunday, January 7, 2018

  4. Pick-up mulch at Zilker park on January 18, 2018. It will be available for free on a first-come, first serve basis. Be sure to bring your own tools and storage containers for loading and transporting the mulch.

  5. Do you live in a house? Skip ahead and read about recycling your Christmas tree at the curb.

Learn About Austin ReBlend Paint

Paint dropped off by customers is inspected before it is chosen to be used in Austin ReBlend. It is then consolidated, blended, filtered and packed by trained personnel to ensure a quality product.

Austin ReBlend paint is free for individuals and nonprofits, and can save residents money when refurbishing their homes. The paint is not available to businesses.

It is available in 3.5 gallon containers and three colors:

  • Texas Limestone (beige)

  • Balcones Canyonland (dark beige)

  • Barton Creek Greenbelt (dark green)

Pick Up Free Mulch

You can pick up mulch for free; however, you must load it yourself. Bring a pitchfork or shovel, work gloves and containers.

", "id": "fff2155d-fc2b-411d-8c3a-1dcef2fff99c"}]

fields.content:
1. Place appliances, furniture, carpet and other bulk items on your curb. Use the “What do I do with” tool to find out what you can bulk pick-up below.

  2. Look up your twice-a-year bulk pick-up weeks with My Collection Schedule. We only collect bulk items from Austin residential trash and recycling customers.

  3. Place bulk items at the curb in front of your house by 6:30 a.m. on the first day of your scheduled collection week.

  4. Separate items into three piles.

    1. Metal - includes appliances, doors must be removed

    2. Passenger car tires - limit of eight tires per household, rims must be removed, no truck or tractor tires

    3. Non-metal items - includes carpeting and nail-free lumber

Do not put bulk items in bags, boxes or other containers. Bags will be treated as extra trash and are subject to extra trash fees.


Items will not be picked up if they are in an alley in any area, including Hyde Park, in front of a vacant lot or in front of a business


To prevent damage to your property, keep bulk items 5 feet away from your:

    1. trash cart

    2. Mailbox

    3. fences or walls

    4. water meter

    5. telephone connection box

    6. parked cars.


Do not place any items under low hanging tree limbs or power lines.


The three separate piles are collected by different trucks and may be collected at different times throughout the week.

{"pk": 5, "path": "000100010002", "depth": 3, "numchild": 0, "title": "Visit the Recycle and Reuse Drop-off Center", "draft_title": "Visit the Recycle and Reuse Drop-off Center", "slug": "dropoff", "content_type": 12, "live": true, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "url_path": "/home/dropoff/", "owner": 1, "seo_title": "", "show_in_menus": false, "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "expire_at": null, "expired": false, "locked": false, "first_published_at": null, "last_published_at": null, "latest_revision_created_at": null, "live_revision": null, "created_at": "2017-12-06T21:02:34.149Z", "updated_at": "2017-12-06T21:02:34.220Z", "content": "

  1. Check below to find out what hazardous waste items are accepted. Some items are free to drop off and some items, like tires, require a fee.

  2. Drop off your household hazardous waste or visit the ReUse Store at 2514 Business Center Dr, Austin, TX 78744.

  3. Be sure to bring products in original containers; do not mix, bring items in 5-gallon (or smaller) containers and put small containers upright in sturdy boxes.

  4. If something is leaking, put it in a container and absorb the spill with cat litter.

", "extra_content": "[{\"type\": \"application_block\", \"value\": 2, \"id\": \"2d3602e3-251a-49ef-9493-132c945fde38\"}, {\"type\": \"application_block\", \"value\": 4, \"id\": \"003658b6-170d-4baf-9c61-848d26511e5f\"}, {\"type\": \"content\", \"value\": \"

Household Hazardous Waste

Throwing household hazardous waste in the trash or pouring it down the drain is dangerous and harmful to the environment. Austin and Travis County residents can drop off hazardous waste for free, up to 30 gallons annually. Large truck or trailer loads will not be accepted after 4:45PM.


Businesses are not eligible to drop off hazardous waste. For information about how businesses can dispose of hazardous waste, call 512-974-4336.

ReUse Store

Many materials that are dropped off at the center are in usable condition. These items go to the ReUse Store, where everyone can pick them up for free. Store items often include:

  • Art supplies

  • Cleaning products

  • Household chemicals

  • Automotive fluids

  • Austin ReBlend paint (link to austintexas.gov page)

  • Mulch


Austin ReBlend paint is free for individuals and nonprofits. It is not available to businesses.

Mulch is free for everyone, but you must load it yourself. Bring a pitchfork or shovel, work gloves and containers.

\", \"id\": \"fff2155d-fc2b-411d-8c3a-1dcef2fff99c\"}]", "topic": 1}

{"pk": 7, "path": "000100010004", "depth": 3, "numchild": 0, "title": "Get Ready for Bulk Item Pick-up", "draft_title": "Get Ready for Bulk Item Pick-up", "slug": "residential-bulk-collection", "content_type": 12, "live": true, "has_unpublished_changes": false, "url_path": "/home/residential-bulk-collection/", "owner": 1, "seo_title": "", "show_in_menus": false, "search_description": "", "go_live_at": null, "expire_at": null, "expired": false, "locked": false, "first_published_at": "2017-12-06T21:05:44.625Z", "last_published_at": "2017-12-06T21:05:44.625Z", "latest_revision_created_at": "2017-12-06T21:05:44.529Z", "live_revision": 4, "created_at": "2017-12-06T21:05:44.483Z", "updated_at": "2017-12-13T22:07:17.666Z", "content": "

  1. Place appliances, furniture, carpet and other bulk items on your curb. Use the \u201cWhat do I do with\u201d tool to find out what you can bulk pick-up below.

  2. Look up your twice-a-year bulk pick-up weeks with My Collection Schedule. We only collect bulk items from Austin residential trash and recycling customers.

  3. Place bulk items at the curb in front of your house by 6:30 a.m. on the first day of your scheduled collection week.

  4. Separate items into three piles.

    1. Metal - includes appliances, doors must be removed

    2. Passenger car tires - limit of eight tires per household, rims must be removed, no truck or tractor tires

    3. Non-metal items - includes carpeting and nail-free lumber

", "content_en": "

  1. Place appliances, furniture, carpet and other bulk items on your curb. Use the \u201cWhat do I do with\u201d tool to find out what you can bulk pick-up below.

", "content_pt": null, "content_es": "", "content_fr": null, "extra_content": "[{\"type\": \"application_block\", \"value\": 2, \"id\": \"ac2d7108-e0ee-4887-b454-b0cdc4886b06\"}, {\"type\": \"application_block\", \"value\": 1, \"id\": \"cb0fc00e-5811-4117-b369-72d9222000ac\"}, {\"type\": \"content\", \"value\": \"

Do not put bulk items in bags, boxes or other containers. Bags will be treated as extra trash and are subject to extra trash fees.


Items will not be picked up if they are in an alley in any area, including Hyde Park, in front of a vacant lot or in front of a business


To prevent damage to your property, keep bulk items 5 feet away from your:

    1. trash cart

    2. Mailbox

    3. fences or walls

    4. water meter

    5. telephone connection box

    6. parked cars.


Do not place any items under low hanging tree limbs or power lines.


The three separate piles are collected by different trucks and may be collected at different times throughout the week.

Learn About Austin ReBlend Paint

Paint dropped off by customers is inspected before it is chosen to be used in Austin ReBlend. It is then consolidated, blended, filtered and packed by trained personnel to ensure a quality product.


Austin ReBlend paint is free for individuals and nonprofits, and can save residents money when refurbishing their homes. The paint is not available to businesses.


It is available in 3.5 gallon containers and three colors:

  • Texas Limestone (beige)

  • Balcones Canyonland (dark beige)

  • Barton Creek Greenbelt (dark green)

Pick Up Free Mulch

You can pick up mulch for free; however, you must load it yourself. Bring a pitchfork or shovel, work gloves and containers.
